    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices of metal or wood with rounded handles and cylindrical shafts that are inserted into holes in pinrails on traditionally rigged sailing ships to secure lines of rigging.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
